5:
There were reports at the Guild of
multiple ashen monsters coming in
here.
9:
They drain mana from people, right?
The fact that they've gathered
together must mean the ashen
savior himself is here...
12:
Everything becomes distorted inside
the Kaleidoscope. It makes for the
perfect hideout.
16:
A labyrinth that changes shape...
Perhaps that's why I couldn't sense
him earlier.
20:
Let us press on. People are still under
attack even as we speak.
28:
Nothing seems out of the ordinary
though.
38:
Fallen angel Olivia... I knew you
would stand in my way again.
40:
Such power... Draining mana from
the masses has worked for you, I see.
42:
But it's not enough... My vessel thirsts
for more.
46:
Why are you doing such a horrible
thing?!
48:
Mortals couldn't be more pitiful.
Their frailty begets the fear of
solitude—too easily are they
crushed by the pain of loss.
49:
Beings so weak that they must
depend on others to survive... Surely
you yourselves would understand...
51:
There is no hope in such a life. I
cannot bear to see such despair. A
purge is the only path forward.
53:
Once I've freed you from your pain
and suffering, all will find
deliverance!
61: Curses... How foul can you be!
63:
Perhaps I should extend the hand of
salvation to you little ones as well.
For all is equal in the face of
destruction.
71:
In truth, they are much stronger
than you believe them to be.
74:
I suppose you and I will never see
things the same way.
86:
Your mana's a part of me now... Cast
aside your pride and bow down to
me.
90:
You're full of openings in your
weakened state. I'll be taking your
mana.
95:
This is bad! I can't believe he's
already drained Olivia of her power!
98:
If we can just get that power back
somehow... I'm sure Olivia will find a
way!
100:
You cling to hope that does not
exist... How pitiful.
102:
Your friends will accept my salvation
soon enough. But first...
104:
Had you been at full strength, you
would have put up a better fight. But
perhaps this is your fate.
111:
Dropping your weapon in the midst
of battle? How foolish. How sad.
115:
I didn't drop it; I merely placed it in
the hands of hope.
121:
I'm borrowing your sword, Olivia!
Haaaagh!
130:
The mana he drained from
everyone is seeping out of him,
including Olivia's!
136:
Thank you, Alk. I shall take it from
here.
139:
This should not be possible...
Mankind is far too weak to resist
salvation...
142:
As you put it, frailty leads to a fear of
solitude. And mortals do indeed find
the pain of loss to be soul-crushing.
146:
But when they are able to overcome
it all, the strength of mankind is
unmatched.
151:
Therein lies their true potential—the
power of hope!
154:
Such hope is meaningless against
what I stand for...
163:
The mana he absorbed is returning
to its rightful owners... Everyone
should be waking up soon!
168:
That little girl's parents should be
okay too!
172:
Indeed... I believe they should now
be conscious.
183:
Yes, the root of the problem is no
more.
187: And I have you to thank for that.
192:
Olivia. Now that you've completed
your mission, will you be returning to
your world?
195:
You came here in pursuit of the
ashen savior after all.
199:
The dimensional pathway I crossed
is no longer open.
201:
I thus have no means of returning
home.
204:
But I'm not worried, and nor should
you be.
206:
Your unwavering courage in this
battle has given me much to
consider.
207:
The power of your hope overcame
the destruction the ashen savior
would have wrought.
209:
I plan on staying in this new world
and seeing for myself what path
hope leads you down.
218:
Until I find a way to return home, I'd
like to stay with you if you'll have me.
